image_analysis.description: A photograph of a small bathroom or water closet. The room features cream-colored paneled walls. A modern white toilet with a bidet-style lid is centered. To the left, there is a toilet paper stand holding two rolls and a toilet brush. To the right, a wall-mounted toilet paper holder and a towel rack with white towels are visible. Two framed pictures hang on the walls; the one on the left shows a beach scene with palm trees and a vehicle, while the one on the right is partially visible. Both pictures have black redaction squares covering portions of the image.
image_analysis.layout: Interior shot of a bathroom stall/closet

notes: The photograph contains black redaction squares over the artwork on the walls. The Bates stamp is located in the bottom right corner.
